## 🔐 v1.3.2 — Public Repository Security Audit Cleanup

This release addresses findings from a comprehensive security audit of the public GitHub repository. All proprietary, confidential, and internal content has been sanitized or removed.

---

### 🗑️ Files Removed (7)

| File | Reason |
|------|--------|
| `CI_DEBT.md` | Internal CI debt tracker with commit hashes, lowered quality gates |
| `CONSOLIDATION-STATUS.md` | Internal project management with upstream source paths |
| `EOF` | Zero-byte junk file |
| `MCP_E2E_PREP.md` | Internal E2E test prep with port configs and agent context |
| `fix_illegal_runes.sh` | Local script with developer username and absolute paths |
| `aegisgate-platform.yaml` | Root-level operational config with ML thresholds, Enterprise feature gates |
| `ui/frontend/consolidated-dashboard.html` | **Hardcoded admin/admin credentials, explicit tier pricing ($49/$199/mo)** |

### 📝 PROPRIETARY Headers Removed (156 Go files)

All `PROPRIETARY - AegisGate Security` + trade secret headers removed to resolve legal contradiction with Apache-2.0 license.

### 💰 Pricing/Commercial Details Sanitized

- Removed `$29/mo`, `$79/mo`, `Custom pricing` from source code comments
- Removed `GetPriceInfo()`, `GeneratePricingReport()` functions
- Removed vendor-specific tier integrations (SIEM providers by tier)
- Removed specific RPM limits from config comments
- Replaced competitor names with generic labels in benchmarks
- Removed tier-gating indicators from README compliance table

### 🔒 Security Fixes

- **Hardcoded JWT secret**: Default `aegisguard-default-secret-change-me` removed → empty string (app fails closed)
- **Grafana default password**: `admin` default removed → requires `GRAFANA_PASSWORD` env var
- **Admin panel URL**: `admin.aegisgatesecurity.io` → `license.aegisgatesecurity.io`
- **License signing format**: `licenseToSign()` function removed from test code

### 🛡️ .gitignore Hardened

Added patterns for all removed files, `docker-compose.override.yml`, `*.tfstate`, `*.tfvars`, `*.kubeconfig`, and organized into clear sections.

### 📚 Post-Audit Fixes

- Docs link updated: `docs.aegisgatesecurity.io` → [GitHub docs/ folder](https://github.com/aegisgatesecurity/aegisgate-platform/tree/main/docs)
- All version references bumped v1.3.1 → **v1.3.2** (21 files)
- `VERSION` file updated to `1.3.2`

